text: Tamas Linder is a computer engineer at Queen's University in Kingston, Ontario. He was named a Fellow of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE) in 2013 for his contributions to source coding and quantization. == References == Category:Fellow Members of the IEEE Category:Queen's University at Kingston faculty Category:Canadian engineers Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
